Html:
Some problems over here. I already have a datapoint style that sets the template. But with line series I only see the datapoints, not the line itself. I thought (and still think) it is the StaggeredStateChange in DataPointSeries that always fires up a storyboard. But it is private method.

When I plot the chart to a seperate window and then save it: all is well.

I created this workaround, not really nice, but it works:
            // create copy of chart.
            Chart dupe = chart.DuplicateChart(model.chartSettings);
            dupe.Width = 700;
            dupe.Height = 500;
            Window win = new Window();
            win.SizeToContent = System.Windows.SizeToContent.WidthAndHeight;
            win.Content = dupe;
            win.ShowInTaskbar = false;
            win.WindowStyle = System.Windows.WindowStyle.None;
            win.AllowsTransparency = true;
            win.Opacity = 0;
            win.Owner = this;
            win.Show();
            this.Focus();
            .....
            Copy to clipboard, save, print...
